"'''The Ordeal of Boba Fett'''" is a short story written by [[Michael Allen Horne]], originally published in the ''[[Dark Empire Sourcebook]]'' and later archived on [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]].

==Plot summary==
Just after the destruction of [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba]] the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt's]] [[Khetanna/Legends|sail barge]], bounty hunter [[Dengar/Legends|Dengar]] stumbles upon a badly wounded [[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]], who has just escaped from the [[Great Pit of Carkoon/Legends|Great Pit of Carkoon]], and transports him to a medical facility for treatment. As Fett lies in a coma, Dengar ponders over his injuries, showing disgust at the damage the [[Sarlacc/Legends|Sarlacc]] had inflicted. After awakening from his coma, both Fett and Dengar leave [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]], bound for [[Nar Shaddaa/Legends|Nar Shaddaa]].

